WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.842 --> 00:00:03.263
<v ->Terri Daniel went through what every parent fears,</v>

2
00:00:03.263 --> 00:00:04.927
the loss of her child.

3
00:00:04.927 --> 00:00:07.018
Her son Danny was dying from a degenerative

4
00:00:07.018 --> 00:00:09.065
metabolic disorder just as Terri

5
00:00:09.065 --> 00:00:11.529
was opening her intuitive abilities.

6
00:00:11.529 --> 00:00:13.289
Terri found that her bond with Danny

7
00:00:13.289 --> 00:00:15.785
exceeded the normal intuitive bond

8
00:00:15.785 --> 00:00:19.249
between mother and child when Danny finally passed over.

9
00:00:19.249 --> 00:00:20.543
From the other side, he began to

10
00:00:20.543 --> 00:00:23.217
teach her about family relationships.

11
00:00:24.542 --> 00:00:29.542 line:15% 
(soothing piano music)

12
00:00:33.044 --> 00:00:35.676
<v Regina>You had a very challenging journey</v>

13
00:00:35.676 --> 00:00:38.064
at one point a few years ago and for several years

14
00:00:38.064 --> 00:00:41.893
prior to that because your son was seriously degenerating

15
00:00:41.893 --> 00:00:45.168
right before your eyes and died at a very tender age

16
00:00:45.168 --> 00:00:47.963
and you weren't even able to communicate with him

17
00:00:47.963 --> 00:00:50.669
at the time of his death and those few years prior

18
00:00:50.669 --> 00:00:53.549
as I understand it, but something happened

19
00:00:53.549 --> 00:00:55.223
once he passed to the other side

20
00:00:55.223 --> 00:00:57.943
and while he was in the degenerative process

21
00:00:57.943 --> 00:01:00.703
to you, can you talk about what happened to your own

22
00:01:00.703 --> 00:01:04.115
intuitive abilities and what was going on with your son

23
00:01:04.115 --> 00:01:06.398
during these final years of his life?

24
00:01:06.398 --> 00:01:10.000
<v ->I was always somewhat intuitive, I was always interested</v>

25
00:01:10.000 --> 00:01:12.699
in spiritual work and metaphysical study,

26
00:01:12.699 --> 00:01:17.095
but when he was about three years out before he died

27
00:01:17.095 --> 00:01:19.637
he started to lose the ability to speak.

28
00:01:19.637 --> 00:01:22.101
He has a progressively degenerative disease,

29
00:01:22.101 --> 00:01:25.045
and as he started losing the ability to speak,

30
00:01:25.045 --> 00:01:29.226
I started gaining the ability to hear telepathically.

31
00:01:29.226 --> 00:01:32.244
We got to a point where we could communicate that way

32
00:01:32.244 --> 00:01:35.145
as any mother can with a nonverbal child,

33
00:01:35.145 --> 00:01:37.396
you can communicate with your infant,

34
00:01:37.396 --> 00:01:39.486
and it kind of went back to that,

35
00:01:39.486 --> 00:01:41.972
but there was a lot more going on.

36
00:01:41.972 --> 00:01:44.894
At the time I was working as a tarot card reader

37
00:01:44.894 --> 00:01:47.689
at a metaphysical bookstore, and I met a woman

38
00:01:47.689 --> 00:01:50.334
who was my mentor, Judy, who said,

39
00:01:50.334 --> 00:01:52.424
"You know when you do these readings,

40
00:01:52.424 --> 00:01:54.739
"you can channel while you're doing them."

41
00:01:54.739 --> 00:01:57.576
I thought, "Oh... okay."

42
00:01:57.576 --> 00:02:00.938
She showed me some exercises and some processes

43
00:02:00.938 --> 00:02:03.129
to open a conduit and begin channeling.

44
00:02:03.129 --> 00:02:06.425
I started bringing in guides and teachers

45
00:02:06.425 --> 00:02:10.585
in dreams and meditations in my tarot reading

46
00:02:10.585 --> 00:02:15.139
and remarkably I found that I could start communicating

47
00:02:15.139 --> 00:02:17.298
with my son that way as well.

48
00:02:17.298 --> 00:02:18.921
<v Regina>And this is when he was still alive?</v>

49
00:02:18.921 --> 00:02:20.947
<v ->Yes, it was three years before he died.</v>

50
00:02:20.947 --> 00:02:24.414
This whole group of teachers and guardians

51
00:02:24.414 --> 00:02:27.656
came and wrapped themselves around us

52
00:02:27.656 --> 00:02:31.208
and led us to the next steps.

53
00:02:31.208 --> 00:02:33.629
Of course they were waiting all along

54
00:02:33.629 --> 00:02:36.371
I just had to open the conduit to hear them.

55
00:02:36.371 --> 00:02:38.688
<v Regina>And what were the next steps?</v>

56
00:02:38.688 --> 00:02:42.182
The next steps were I began to teach my son

57
00:02:42.182 --> 00:02:45.595
to meditate and also teach him different views of death.

58
00:02:45.595 --> 00:02:48.272
I realized that children in America, their only

59
00:02:48.272 --> 00:02:51.941
idea of death is what they see on TV and the movies.

60
00:02:51.941 --> 00:02:53.876
<v Regina>And you knew at this time he was going to die?</v>

61
00:02:53.876 --> 00:02:55.955
<v ->I knew when he was 10 that he was going to die</v>

62
00:02:55.955 --> 00:02:58.514
and at this point he was now 12 or 13.

63
00:02:58.514 --> 00:03:01.832
So I thought, okay I'm going to have to talk to him

64
00:03:01.832 --> 00:03:03.981
about this, I'm going to have to explain it to him.

65
00:03:03.981 --> 00:03:06.047
We never had any relatives who died,

66
00:03:06.047 --> 00:03:08.607
we never had a dog who died, so he knew nothing

67
00:03:08.607 --> 00:03:13.607
except video games and movies. Violence, rage.

68
00:03:14.181 --> 00:03:17.416
The first thing, the next step was to give him

69
00:03:17.416 --> 00:03:19.089
a different view of death.

70
00:03:19.089 --> 00:03:21.126
I started getting books from the library and

71
00:03:21.126 --> 00:03:23.196
websites with Native American views

72
00:03:23.196 --> 00:03:25.467
and Buddhist views and teaching it to him

73
00:03:25.467 --> 00:03:29.211
and reading him stories and also imparting

74
00:03:29.211 --> 00:03:33.734
my existing beliefs about reincarnation and the afterlife

75
00:03:33.734 --> 00:03:38.734
and teaching him when you die, it's gonna be like

76
00:03:38.981 --> 00:03:42.885
you just go to sleep and then you wake up in another world,

77
00:03:42.885 --> 00:03:45.744
but in this world, your body is perfect,

78
00:03:45.744 --> 00:03:48.133
you feel absolute joy, and guess what?

79
00:03:48.133 --> 00:03:52.171
I will still be there with you, and you'll say,

80
00:03:52.171 --> 00:03:56.307
"Wow, I'm gone, but I'm not gone, I'm here even more."

81
00:03:56.307 --> 00:03:59.272
With that I started giving him guided meditations

82
00:03:59.272 --> 00:04:01.224
and teaching him all of this because I wanted him

83
00:04:01.224 --> 00:04:05.120
to have a happy death, I didn't want him to be afraid.

84
00:04:06.890 --> 00:04:08.386
<v Regina>You were communicating, by this time,</v>

85
00:04:08.386 --> 00:04:11.237
telepathically with him in terms of your hearing,

86
00:04:11.237 --> 00:04:13.541
but in terms of your verbalization

87
00:04:13.541 --> 00:04:15.994
of these various traditions and stories

88
00:04:15.994 --> 00:04:18.458
that you had just mentioned, were you getting

89
00:04:18.458 --> 00:04:22.319
validation from him that he was really understanding

90
00:04:22.319 --> 00:04:25.700
and embracing this information and interested in it?

91
00:04:25.700 --> 00:04:27.652
<v ->That's a really good question because</v>

92
00:04:27.652 --> 00:04:31.064
he couldn't say to me, "This is cool" or "Yes I get this"

93
00:04:31.064 --> 00:04:33.984
but yes, I was and I was getting that validation

94
00:04:33.984 --> 00:04:36.192
emotionally and telepathically.

95
00:04:36.192 --> 00:04:38.997
When I would do a guided meditation with him

96
00:04:38.997 --> 00:04:41.248
he couldn't keep his eyes closed because

97
00:04:41.248 --> 00:04:44.021
neurologically he was having seizures all the time

98
00:04:44.021 --> 00:04:45.523
so I would say, "Okay close your eyes"

99
00:04:45.523 --> 00:04:48.291
and he would go like this and he would open them again.

100
00:04:48.291 --> 00:04:49.109
<v Regina>Yeah.</v>

101
00:04:49.109 --> 00:04:50.045
(both laugh)

102
00:04:50.045 --> 00:04:52.485
<v ->But he was trying to close his eyes,</v>

103
00:04:52.485 --> 00:04:55.920
so I knew he was listening and he'd be smiling

104
00:04:55.920 --> 00:05:00.121
and he would just be in this blissful space

105
00:05:00.121 --> 00:05:02.274
and I could feel it, and I could feel his soul

106
00:05:02.274 --> 00:05:05.824
and I would have dreams, or I'd fall asleep next to him

107
00:05:05.824 --> 00:05:09.108
and I'd have these incredible visions and dreams

108
00:05:09.108 --> 00:05:13.566
of his soul and my soul dancing over mountaintops

109
00:05:13.566 --> 00:05:17.138
with bells ringing in the background, just amazing stuff.

110
00:05:17.138 --> 00:05:19.791
So I knew he was getting in.

111
00:05:19.791 --> 00:05:22.990
[Regina] So by the time he had lost his ability to speak

112
00:05:22.990 --> 00:05:25.502
he was still very young, like you said

113
00:05:25.502 --> 00:05:28.478
by the age of 11 or 12 he was having difficulty?

114
00:05:28.478 --> 00:05:30.888
<v ->He started having difficulty about 11</v>

115
00:05:30.888 --> 00:05:34.227
and by 13 or 14 he couldn't really talk at all.

116
00:05:34.227 --> 00:05:35.923
<v Regina>So he never reached an age where</v>

117
00:05:35.923 --> 00:05:37.905
he would have been able to articulate

118
00:05:37.905 --> 00:05:40.177
the kind of things that happened then

119
00:05:40.177 --> 00:05:43.452
once he made his transition into the other world, right?

120
00:05:43.452 --> 00:05:45.798
<v ->Yes and that's a problem for me.</v>

121
00:05:45.798 --> 00:05:47.772
That's one of the things I still struggle with,

122
00:05:47.772 --> 00:05:50.907
with guilt because all bereaved parents have guilt,

123
00:05:50.907 --> 00:05:53.574
and I wish that I had started talking to him about this

124
00:05:53.574 --> 00:05:56.016
when he was still able to talk.

125
00:05:56.016 --> 00:05:57.844
He was diagnosed when he was 10.

126
00:05:57.844 --> 00:05:59.022
<v Regina>What did he have again?</v>

127
00:05:59.022 --> 00:06:01.530
<v ->It was called metachromatic leukodystrophy.</v>

128
00:06:01.530 --> 00:06:05.054
It's a very rare disease, one in 80,000 births,

129
00:06:05.054 --> 00:06:10.028
and it takes an exact genetic lineup between parents

130
00:06:10.028 --> 00:06:13.438
for it to happen, it was hereditary and he was adopted.

131
00:06:13.438 --> 00:06:16.062
<v Regina>It's a metabolic disorder, it's a degenerative</v>

132
00:06:16.062 --> 00:06:17.853
metabolic disorder, is it not?

133
00:06:17.853 --> 00:06:21.245
<v ->Sort of, it's a myelin demyelination,</v>

134
00:06:21.245 --> 00:06:24.604
the myelin sheath of the brain disappears kind of disorder.

135
00:06:24.604 --> 00:06:25.927
<v Regina>Right, right.</v>

136
00:06:25.927 --> 00:06:29.178
<v ->I always thought, I wish I had started talking to him</v>

137
00:06:29.178 --> 00:06:31.268
about this when he was 10, because then

138
00:06:31.268 --> 00:06:33.401
he could tell me what he thought about death.

139
00:06:33.401 --> 00:06:35.844
But when he was 10, I wasn't ready to tell him,

140
00:06:35.844 --> 00:06:38.137
"You're gonna die" because I didn't want him

141
00:06:38.137 --> 00:06:40.526
to worry about it, so I didn't really

142
00:06:40.526 --> 00:06:44.056
start telling him that until he was 12 and 13.

143
00:06:44.056 --> 00:06:46.657
By that time he couldn't respond verbally

144
00:06:46.657 --> 00:06:48.726
to me so that's something I regret.

145
00:06:48.726 --> 00:06:52.001
When I work with parents now of severely disabled

146
00:06:52.001 --> 00:06:54.273
children with life threatening diseases, I always

147
00:06:54.273 --> 00:06:57.962
tell them, "Talk about this while they can still talk."

148
00:06:57.962 --> 00:07:00.799
But most of the parents say, "Oh no, I can't."

149
00:07:00.799 --> 00:07:02.772
Same reason I couldn't.

150
00:07:02.772 --> 00:07:06.463
<v Regina>I understand. Yes. Let's move into the time</v>

151
00:07:06.463 --> 00:07:09.919
where he did make his transition from this world to the next

152
00:07:09.919 --> 00:07:12.873
and then what started happening.

153
00:07:12.873 --> 00:07:17.308
<v ->Well it turns out that all the training I did</v>

154
00:07:17.308 --> 00:07:20.027
for both of us, which it turns out it was,

155
00:07:20.027 --> 00:07:23.912
all those meditations and conversations and the dreams,

156
00:07:23.912 --> 00:07:27.769
I would sleep by his side and we would journey together.

157
00:07:27.769 --> 00:07:31.599
30 minutes after he died, I was holding his body

158
00:07:31.599 --> 00:07:34.339
in my arms and I said, "Where are you?

159
00:07:34.339 --> 00:07:36.291
"can you show me where you are?"

160
00:07:36.291 --> 00:07:38.594
and he sent me this ridiculous vision.

161
00:07:38.594 --> 00:07:40.546
It was a picture of him standing in about

162
00:07:40.546 --> 00:07:43.789
two inches of water, kicking his feet and laughing

163
00:07:43.789 --> 00:07:46.466
and he's wearing a t-shirt with rolled up sleeves

164
00:07:46.466 --> 00:07:48.717
and pants with rolled up cuffs

165
00:07:48.717 --> 00:07:50.862
and he looked like James Dean in Rebel Without a Cause

166
00:07:50.862 --> 00:07:51.862
(Regina laughs)

167
00:07:51.862 --> 00:07:54.370
and I laughed my head off, I just thought that was so funny

168
00:07:54.370 --> 00:07:55.906
and I said, "Why are you showing me this?"

169
00:07:55.906 --> 00:07:57.782
and he said, "Because I want you to laugh.

170
00:07:57.782 --> 00:08:01.643
"I want you to see how much fun this is."

171
00:08:01.643 --> 00:08:03.286
<v Regina>And you were hearing him?</v>

172
00:08:03.286 --> 00:08:05.056
<v ->I was totally hearing him, and this was</v>

173
00:08:05.056 --> 00:08:07.792
30 minutes after he died, but the hearing

174
00:08:07.792 --> 00:08:10.001
isn't like you're hearing me right now.

175
00:08:10.001 --> 00:08:15.001
It's not sound in your ears. It's thoughts in your head.

176
00:08:16.476 --> 00:08:18.890
They were so clear and so articulate

177
00:08:18.890 --> 00:08:21.672
and he was very articulate when he could talk,

178
00:08:21.672 --> 00:08:23.763
and he turned out to be extremely articulate

179
00:08:23.763 --> 00:08:27.585
on the other side as well and he said,

180
00:08:27.585 --> 00:08:30.522
"Well here we are. We've planned this.

181
00:08:30.522 --> 00:08:35.470
"We worked on this, now the fun and games can begin.

182
00:08:35.470 --> 00:08:37.838
"This is what we're really here to do,

183
00:08:37.838 --> 00:08:40.280
"so let's get started. We've got work to do."

184
00:08:40.280 --> 00:08:42.433
<v Regina>Let's talk about where the work began.</v>

185
00:08:42.433 --> 00:08:44.133
(both laugh)

186
00:08:44.133 --> 00:08:45.900
<v ->In the beginning I started seeing him</v>

187
00:08:45.900 --> 00:08:49.548
and hearing him all the time and he introduced me

188
00:08:49.548 --> 00:08:52.364
to somebody else that he was with on the other side,

189
00:08:52.364 --> 00:08:54.564
a man that I first saw...

190
00:08:54.564 --> 00:08:58.104
well he showed me this vineyard,

191
00:08:58.104 --> 00:09:00.877
this sun-drenched beautiful yellow light

192
00:09:00.877 --> 00:09:05.877
Italian vineyard and in a tree

193
00:09:06.288 --> 00:09:09.864
was this man who was working, picking fruit or something,

194
00:09:09.864 --> 00:09:13.480
and it was one of my guides, somebody named Arlin.

195
00:09:13.480 --> 00:09:15.880
Danny started introducing me to all of these people.

196
00:09:15.880 --> 00:09:17.152
It had now gotten to the point where I was

197
00:09:17.152 --> 00:09:20.100
getting these huge visuals and these magnificent stories

198
00:09:20.100 --> 00:09:23.766
from him and I would write them all down in my journal.

199
00:09:23.766 --> 00:09:26.218
So he introduced me to Arlin and a bunch of other people

200
00:09:26.218 --> 00:09:28.136
who were with him, and he started teaching me

201
00:09:28.136 --> 00:09:32.222
about soul families, and how incarnations are planned,

202
00:09:32.222 --> 00:09:34.152
"All the people here right now

203
00:09:34.152 --> 00:09:35.688
are members of our soul family.

204
00:09:35.688 --> 00:09:38.152
"Some of us are incarnated together now

205
00:09:38.152 --> 00:09:40.488
"or at other times, we sort of pop in and out,

206
00:09:40.488 --> 00:09:43.112
"and in-between incarnations we sit

207
00:09:43.112 --> 00:09:45.767
"and we have these conferences,"

208
00:09:45.767 --> 00:09:47.527
this is how he put it, and he showed me

209
00:09:47.527 --> 00:09:49.435
a beautiful little stone cottage in the middle

210
00:09:49.435 --> 00:09:51.451
of this vineyard with a big table

211
00:09:51.451 --> 00:09:53.521
and everybody's sitting around the table.

212
00:09:53.521 --> 00:09:55.717
I'm not saying that's the way it always happens

213
00:09:55.717 --> 00:09:59.044
but he showed it to me in a way that I would understand,

214
00:09:59.044 --> 00:10:00.015
<v Regina>Right.</v>

215
00:10:00.015 --> 00:10:01.574
<v ->which is how they communicate with us.</v>

216
00:10:01.574 --> 00:10:03.523
They'll give us whatever vision works for us.

217
00:10:03.523 --> 00:10:06.584
If we want to see Jesus and Saint Peter

218
00:10:06.584 --> 00:10:10.009
and pearly gates, this is what we'll see.

219
00:10:10.009 --> 00:10:11.012
<v Regina>Whatever we're going to relate to</v>

220
00:10:11.012 --> 00:10:13.241
and feel comfortable with, comforted by.

221
00:10:13.241 --> 00:10:15.214
<v ->Yes, whatever communicates with us.</v>

222
00:10:15.214 --> 00:10:16.761
There were reasons why these elements

223
00:10:16.761 --> 00:10:19.208
worked for me and he knew that.

224
00:10:19.208 --> 00:10:21.666
He started to teach me stuff, he said,

225
00:10:21.666 --> 00:10:24.247
"Start writing this down, get a tape recorder.

226
00:10:24.247 --> 00:10:25.919
"You're gonna be hearing from me a lot."

227
00:10:25.919 --> 00:10:28.452
<v Regina>Let's start talking about what he was telling you</v>

228
00:10:28.452 --> 00:10:32.493
about how people come together into relationship,

229
00:10:32.493 --> 00:10:35.525
how family comes together and so forth.

230
00:10:35.525 --> 00:10:37.039
<v ->I wish I had a copy of the book with me</v>

231
00:10:37.039 --> 00:10:39.055
because I could read you this great quote.

232
00:10:39.055 --> 00:10:43.095
All members of a family are there by agreement

233
00:10:43.095 --> 00:10:47.340
to work out certain issues that you want to work with.

234
00:10:47.340 --> 00:10:50.891
For example, if we're sitting at the cosmic conference table

235
00:10:50.891 --> 00:10:55.149
right now, I might be saying to you,

236
00:10:55.149 --> 00:10:57.371
"I really need to work on greed.

237
00:10:57.371 --> 00:10:58.800
"I've got some stuff with that." and so you

238
00:10:58.800 --> 00:11:01.433
might say to me, "Let's plan this out."

239
00:11:01.433 --> 00:11:03.289
It's like rolling a map out on the table,

240
00:11:03.289 --> 00:11:05.124
and you'll say, "I'll tell you what, how about

241
00:11:05.124 --> 00:11:07.767
"I'll incarnate as your rich uncle

242
00:11:07.767 --> 00:11:09.580
"and I'll leave you out of my will."

243
00:11:09.580 --> 00:11:11.063
Someone else will pipe in and say,

244
00:11:11.063 --> 00:11:14.900
"I'll be the abusive mother who neglects and abuses you

245
00:11:14.900 --> 00:11:17.684
"and that way you can learn about self sufficiency."

246
00:11:17.684 --> 00:11:19.306
Somebody else will throw in something else

247
00:11:19.306 --> 00:11:21.140
and that's how we plan our incarnation.

248
00:11:21.140 --> 00:11:24.313
Here we are, we pop into Earth and we've got this family

