<v Regina>I don't think so.</v>

755
00:34:23.879 --> 00:34:24.669
<v ->Not everybody does this.</v>

756
00:34:24.669 --> 00:34:25.669
<v Regina>Yet, another person I spoke with</v>

757
00:34:25.669 --> 00:34:27.709
right after they died stayed fully mature,

758
00:34:27.709 --> 00:34:29.650
awake, and was quite a rascal.

759
00:34:29.650 --> 00:34:31.561
I said, "Where'd you hide the money?"

760
00:34:31.561 --> 00:34:32.671
(Regina laughs)

761
00:34:32.671 --> 00:34:33.988
and he showed me where the money was hidden

762
00:34:33.988 --> 00:34:36.036
so his wife could have the advantage of it,

763
00:34:36.036 --> 00:34:37.871
because he had hidden it from her too.

764
00:34:37.871 --> 00:34:39.012
<v ->And you found the money?</v>

765
00:34:39.012 --> 00:34:39.820
<v Regina>Yeah, oh yeah.</v>

766
00:34:39.820 --> 00:34:40.734
<v ->Wow, that's great.</v>

767
00:34:40.734 --> 00:34:41.833
<v Regina>But that was within 24 hours of</v>

768
00:34:41.833 --> 00:34:44.659
his death, so he was very available.

769
00:34:44.659 --> 00:34:45.695
<v ->He was prepared--</v>

770
00:34:45.695 --> 00:34:46.545
<v Regina>He was totally prepared.</v>

771
00:34:46.545 --> 00:34:47.501
<v ->because this is something that he planned.</v>

772
00:34:47.501 --> 00:34:49.364
In a coma for three months prior, too.

773
00:34:49.364 --> 00:34:50.255
<v ->Wow.</v>

774
00:34:50.255 --> 00:34:51.398
<v Regina>Very interesting but also</v>

775
00:34:51.398 --> 00:34:54.123
a little more advanced in those understandings.

776
00:34:54.123 --> 00:34:56.294
Each one, it's a different journey.

777
00:34:56.294 --> 00:35:01.009
Each one of us here has the ability to connect.

778
00:35:01.009 --> 00:35:04.404
What do you do when you begin the process

779
00:35:04.404 --> 00:35:06.665
of showing someone that they can do this,

780
00:35:06.665 --> 00:35:08.403
how does that start for most people?

781
00:35:08.403 --> 00:35:10.771
<v ->If I was working with someone one-on-one</v>

782
00:35:10.771 --> 00:35:12.531
like someone who came to me as a client

783
00:35:12.531 --> 00:35:15.923
or a group if I was doing a six week workshop,

784
00:35:15.923 --> 00:35:19.709
I would start of course by giving them

785
00:35:19.709 --> 00:35:21.779
books to read and material to study,

786
00:35:21.779 --> 00:35:23.048
that would be the first place.

787
00:35:23.048 --> 00:35:25.728
Just to sort of see where they are

788
00:35:25.728 --> 00:35:26.989
because there's such good information

789
00:35:26.989 --> 00:35:29.634
out there, there's a lot of good books

790
00:35:29.634 --> 00:35:31.511
and a lot of good places to start.

791
00:35:31.511 --> 00:35:34.252
Along the way I would also walk them through

792
00:35:34.252 --> 00:35:36.791
various guided meditations that start out

793
00:35:36.791 --> 00:35:40.919
very simple of just breathing and feeling.

794
00:35:40.919 --> 00:35:43.937
I have real special music that I use

795
00:35:43.937 --> 00:35:48.118
that I search high and low over the internet for

796
00:35:48.118 --> 00:35:51.201
meditation music and I can find this music

797
00:35:51.201 --> 00:35:53.899
that's so rare and so amazing.

798
00:35:53.899 --> 00:35:55.638
<v Regina>This is important in a lot of different</v>

799
00:35:55.638 --> 00:35:58.614
beliefs, disciplines, cultures and so forth,

800
00:35:58.614 --> 00:36:00.815
the music that's used when you're trying to connect.

801
00:36:00.815 --> 00:36:02.632
<v ->I think so, and I'm not really much</v>

802
00:36:02.632 --> 00:36:05.043
of a music person, but when I started doing this work

803
00:36:05.043 --> 00:36:08.611
music became so important and I have found music

804
00:36:08.611 --> 00:36:11.259
that I don't even know how it comes to me.

805
00:36:11.259 --> 00:36:14.982
I find it online, I find this rare CD of meditation music

806
00:36:14.982 --> 00:36:18.576
that you can only buy in England, and it costs $45

807
00:36:18.576 --> 00:36:21.648
and I order the CD and I can never find it again.

808
00:36:21.648 --> 00:36:23.547
People ask me, "Where did you find that?"

809
00:36:23.547 --> 00:36:25.797
and I say, "Here's what it is. Go look for it."

810
00:36:25.797 --> 00:36:28.421
Nobody can find it. I don't even know how it comes to me.

811
00:36:28.421 --> 00:36:30.949
The music and the breathing is really important.

812
00:36:30.949 --> 00:36:35.640
It's basically hypnotherapy, it just puts you into a state,

813
00:36:35.640 --> 00:36:40.244
a heightened state and visualization, very simple stuff.

814
00:36:40.244 --> 00:36:43.145
Walking through a meadow, somebody's standing there.

815
00:36:43.145 --> 00:36:45.811
They give you something, what did they give you?

816
00:36:45.811 --> 00:36:47.134
They're saying something to you,

817
00:36:47.134 --> 00:36:49.363
what do you hear them say?

818
00:36:49.363 --> 00:36:50.803
Before I do these meditations,

819
00:36:50.803 --> 00:36:54.362
I prepare them with a list of things to watch out for.

820
00:36:55.922 --> 00:36:58.690
You're not gonna see flying tables and flickering lights,

821
00:36:58.690 --> 00:37:00.620
though you might, some people do.

822
00:37:00.620 --> 00:37:03.148
You're not gonna probably hear verbal

823
00:37:03.148 --> 00:37:06.543
words that your ears can hear.

824
00:37:07.123 --> 00:37:09.940
They talk to us in symbols.

825
00:37:09.940 --> 00:37:13.090
If you meet a guide in this meditation

826
00:37:13.090 --> 00:37:15.948
or your dead father, he might hand you

827
00:37:15.948 --> 00:37:20.948
a belt buckle or a hair brush. Don't dismiss that.

828
00:37:21.132 --> 00:37:23.201
In our minds, what we do because the ego

829
00:37:23.201 --> 00:37:25.633
is always in control, or tries to be, it's like,

830
00:37:25.633 --> 00:37:27.702
"That's just a belt buckle, that doesn't mean anything."

831
00:37:27.702 --> 00:37:29.793
Then you shut it down, and it's gone.

832
00:37:29.793 --> 00:37:32.479
I walk them through a process of learning

833
00:37:32.479 --> 00:37:35.338
to accept whatever they get, and if the being

834
00:37:35.338 --> 00:37:38.074
whoever it is says to them,

835
00:37:40.186 --> 00:37:41.816
"Black shoe on a pink floor"

836
00:37:41.816 --> 00:37:44.813
or some ridiculous thing, allow that to be true.

837
00:37:44.813 --> 00:37:47.480
I also have them write everything down

838
00:37:47.480 --> 00:37:49.410
that they hear or experience.

839
00:37:49.410 --> 00:37:51.458
<v Regina>This is critical. Allowing themselves</v>

840
00:37:51.458 --> 00:37:53.612
to take it in without invalidating.

841
00:37:53.612 --> 00:37:56.866
I think that's probably one of the most critical things.

842
00:37:56.866 --> 00:37:59.159
<v ->Before I will even walk them through</v>

843
00:37:59.159 --> 00:38:01.900
a meditation like this, I put them through this checklist

844
00:38:01.900 --> 00:38:04.438
of all the things to watch out for, and

845
00:38:04.438 --> 00:38:06.668
they get it, they do really well at it.

846
00:38:06.668 --> 00:38:08.748
In most of my groups, at least half

847
00:38:08.748 --> 00:38:11.702
of the people make contact easily,

848
00:38:11.702 --> 00:38:13.697
and they're amazed at what they get.

849
00:38:13.697 --> 00:38:15.136
<v Regina>And the other half could</v>

850
00:38:15.136 --> 00:38:16.854
if they had the confidence in themselves

851
00:38:16.854 --> 00:38:18.646
and were not invalidating what's coming along

852
00:38:18.646 --> 00:38:20.715
among whatever else may be going on

853
00:38:20.715 --> 00:38:22.475
in their lives, fears of some kind

854
00:38:22.475 --> 00:38:24.587
and whatever blocks us from learning.

855
00:38:24.587 --> 00:38:26.101
<v ->That's absolutely true.</v>

856
00:38:26.101 --> 00:38:27.562
<v Regina>So you're saying every human being</v>

857
00:38:27.562 --> 00:38:29.717
does have the capability of doing this?

858
00:38:29.717 --> 00:38:32.693
<v ->Absolutely. The beings around us in the higher realms,</v>

859
00:38:32.693 --> 00:38:35.082
our loved ones, our guides, are standing there

860
00:38:35.082 --> 00:38:36.778
next to us all the time going,

861
00:38:36.778 --> 00:38:39.644
"I'm here! Can't you see me?"

862
00:38:40.774 --> 00:38:42.105
They're always out there, they're always

863
00:38:42.105 --> 00:38:45.467
wanting to talk to us, but they're also infinitely patient,

864
00:38:45.467 --> 00:38:48.646
because if there's no time, you can't be impatient.

865
00:38:48.646 --> 00:38:50.534
I say that to my son a lot because sometimes

866
00:38:50.534 --> 00:38:53.456
I'll really feel him calling me, there'll be some message

867
00:38:53.456 --> 00:38:56.037
that he's trying to give me, and I'm busy.

868
00:38:56.037 --> 00:38:58.352
The way I talk to him is I journal.

869
00:38:58.352 --> 00:39:01.765
I hear him all the time, but when something big comes

870
00:39:01.765 --> 00:39:03.909
I have to sit down at my computer

871
00:39:03.909 --> 00:39:06.298
and he just starts writing through me.

872
00:39:06.298 --> 00:39:08.506
I'll say, "I feel you calling me, I know you're

873
00:39:08.506 --> 00:39:10.618
"trying to tell me something, but

874
00:39:10.618 --> 00:39:12.928
"I can't do it right now, can you wait?"

875
00:39:12.928 --> 00:39:13.561
(Regina laughs)

876
00:39:13.561 --> 00:39:16.718
Then I feel bad and guilty, so the next time I talk to him

877
00:39:16.718 --> 00:39:21.176
I'll say, "Do you feel bad that I push you away sometimes?"

878
00:39:21.176 --> 00:39:24.953
and he says, "How can I be impatient if there's no time?"

879
00:39:24.953 --> 00:39:26.663
<v Regina>(laughs) very true</v>

880
00:39:26.663 --> 00:39:29.651
There has to be time to be impatient.

881
00:39:29.651 --> 00:39:31.678
All the time in the world, everything's broadcasting

882
00:39:31.678 --> 00:39:36.360
at you constantly, you can receive it at your own pace.

883
00:39:36.360 --> 00:39:39.449
<v Regina>Yes. You call the book A Swan in Heaven</v>

884
00:39:39.449 --> 00:39:42.265
and I see you have a swan necklace on,

885
00:39:42.265 --> 00:39:44.888
why A Swan in Heaven?

886
00:39:44.888 --> 00:39:49.333
<v ->(sighs) When he was 11 years old, it was</v>

887
00:39:49.333 --> 00:39:51.861
when September 11th happened, and

888
00:39:51.861 --> 00:39:53.514
I was watching a documentary on TV

889
00:39:53.514 --> 00:39:56.319
about the firefighters whose partners had died,

890
00:39:56.319 --> 00:39:58.804
and the firefighters felt guilty that

891
00:39:58.804 --> 00:40:00.991
they hadn't saved their partners,

892
00:40:00.991 --> 00:40:03.124
and they went and got tattoos of

893
00:40:03.124 --> 00:40:05.791
their partners' face on their backs.

894
00:40:05.791 --> 00:40:09.044
Full shoulder to shoulder neck to waist tattoos

895
00:40:09.044 --> 00:40:11.230
so that they felt like their partner

896
00:40:11.230 --> 00:40:12.990
was with them all the time.

897
00:40:12.990 --> 00:40:14.985
I saw this and I said, "That's great,

898
00:40:14.985 --> 00:40:17.566
"I have to get a tattoo for Danny."

899
00:40:17.566 --> 00:40:19.976
I asked him, when he could still talk,

900
00:40:19.976 --> 00:40:22.163
if you could be any animal, what would you be?

901
00:40:22.163 --> 00:40:23.497
He said a swan.

902
00:40:23.497 --> 00:40:24.560
<v Regina>Aw.</v>

903
00:40:24.560 --> 00:40:27.019
<v ->I thought, he's an 11 year old boy,</v>

904
00:40:27.019 --> 00:40:28.545
why would he pick a swan?

905
00:40:28.545 --> 00:40:33.195
A wolf, a dinosaur, a dragon, a swan?

906
00:40:33.195 --> 00:40:36.096
So I asked him 10 times, "Are you sure?"

907
00:40:36.096 --> 00:40:38.603
I didn't even know he knew what a swan was.

908
00:40:38.603 --> 00:40:41.365
I was pretty sure he'd never seen one.

909
00:40:41.365 --> 00:40:44.106
I kept saying, "Are you sure?" and he said, "Yes, a swan."

910
00:40:44.106 --> 00:40:48.767
So I got a tattoo of a swan and I bought this

911
00:40:48.767 --> 00:40:51.826
and now I have this whole swan thing.

912
00:40:51.826 --> 00:40:55.156
I began researching what does swan mean

913
00:40:55.156 --> 00:40:57.759
in various cultures, and I found out

914
00:40:57.759 --> 00:40:59.593
that in the Keltic culture and also

915
00:40:59.593 --> 00:41:01.407
in the Native American culture

916
00:41:01.407 --> 00:41:03.870
and probably many others, it means transition.

917
00:41:03.870 --> 00:41:07.085
The ugly duckling turns into a swan.

918
00:41:07.085 --> 00:41:12.018
In the medicine cards, the swan travels between two worlds.

919
00:41:12.018 --> 00:41:14.663
It goes into dream time, from Earth

920
00:41:14.663 --> 00:41:16.732
to dream time with a dragonfly.

921
00:41:16.732 --> 00:41:18.076
There's this whole story.

922
00:41:18.076 --> 00:41:22.737
So he knew that a swan was about moving between worlds.

923
00:41:22.737 --> 00:41:23.857
<v Regina>How perfect.</v>

924
00:41:23.857 --> 00:41:26.108
<v ->So that's why the book is called that.</v>

925
00:41:26.108 --> 00:41:27.270
<v Regina>Any final thoughts because</v>

926
00:41:27.270 --> 00:41:29.542
we can let people pick up a copy of the book

927
00:41:29.542 --> 00:41:33.446
to get the full detailed experiences and dialoge

928
00:41:33.446 --> 00:41:35.163
that was going on between you and your son

929
00:41:35.163 --> 00:41:38.043
on these really very critical subjects

930
00:41:38.043 --> 00:41:39.856
that all of us, areas of life,

931
00:41:39.856 --> 00:41:41.851
every one of us has to interface with.

932
00:41:41.851 --> 00:41:44.123
You have a new book coming out also in Spring

933
00:41:44.123 --> 00:41:48.773
of 2010 about embracing death and the nuances there.

934
00:41:48.773 --> 00:41:53.090
So any final thoughts you have before we wrap it up?

935
00:41:53.090 --> 00:41:56.684
<v ->I think that if I could say one thing to the world,</v>

936
00:41:56.684 --> 00:42:01.462
it would be we're not alone. We're not alone here.

937
00:42:01.462 --> 00:42:03.862
UFO people say that all the time,

938
00:42:03.862 --> 00:42:08.086
but it's much more than that. Marianne Williamson said,

939
00:42:08.086 --> 00:42:11.680
"If you had any idea who was walking with you,

940
00:42:11.680 --> 00:42:14.422
"you would never be afraid of anything."

941
00:42:14.422 --> 00:42:17.438
I would add to that: least of all, death.

942
00:42:17.438 --> 00:42:21.654
Death is just like walking into the next room.

943
00:42:21.654 --> 00:42:26.193
When you lose your fear of death, you lose your fear.

944
00:42:27.963 --> 00:42:32.963
Fear of death is the core of all neurosis in human life.

945
00:42:33.658 --> 00:42:36.228
The ego just wants to survive,

946
00:42:36.228 --> 00:42:38.422
the ego just wants to be in control.

947
00:42:38.422 --> 00:42:42.692
With that craving for control and security

948
00:42:42.692 --> 00:42:45.668
we create greed, manipulation,

949
00:42:45.668 --> 00:42:49.476
rape, violence, all of that stuff.

950
00:42:49.476 --> 00:42:53.091
It really comes from the ego's fear of disappearance.

951
00:42:53.091 --> 00:42:55.534
When you realize that your essence

952
00:42:55.534 --> 00:42:58.428
cannot ever disappear, what could

953
00:42:58.428 --> 00:43:01.532
there possibly be to be afraid of?

954
00:43:01.532 --> 00:43:03.718
<v Regina>So well said. Thank you so much</v>

955
00:43:03.718 --> 00:43:05.477
for your time, Terri. I really appreciate

956
00:43:05.477 --> 00:43:08.058
you telling us this beautiful story.

957
00:43:08.058 --> 00:43:10.610
<v ->Thank you. Thank you Regina.</v>

